99565.name: First child SRB (Jiang et al. 2017)
99565.description: Sex ratio at birth (SRB) of the first-born child. SRB is measured as the number of male births per 100 female births. The natural 'sex ratio at birth' is noted to be 105 male births per 100 female births.
99565.datasetName: Sex ratio at birth by birth order in S.Korea & China (Jiang et al. 2017)
99565.s_name: Sex ratio at birth by birth order in S.Korea & China (Jiang et al. 2017)

source.name: Sex ratio at birth by birth order in S.Korea & China (Jiang et al. 2017)
source.dataPublishedBy: Jiang, Q., Yu, Q., Yang, S., & Sánchez-Barricarte, J. J. (2017). Changes in sex ratio at birth in china: a decomposition by birth order. Journal of Biosocial Science, 49(6), 826-841.
source.additionalInfo:
Data measures the sex ratio at birth (SRB) depending on the birth order of children (first, second or third-born child). SRB is measured as the number of male births per 100 female births. The natural 'sex ratio at birth' is noted to be 105 male births per 100 female births.

Data is available for South Korea and China.
